PrecisAmendment to the SPECIAL DUTY AREA PENSION ORDER which adds the Republic of Mozambique to the schedule of duty areas designated as a "Special Service Area", commencing February 8, 1993, the day upon which Canadian Forces began to participate in United Nations military observer activities.
